      "content": "you say the only thing that matters is that i'm still here, but why? if being \"here\" just means being a vessel for this constant, unyielding agony, then being here feels more like a punishment than a life. is it really \"dignity\" to just suffer indefinitely when there's no light at the end of the tunnel? it feels more like just... staying in a room that's on fire.",
